<subSubSection id="C36C06CEFFE4FFF87BDCFBC5A0E98775" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE4FFF87BDCFBC5A024873D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,1986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87BDCFBC5A02E8455" bold="true" box="[199,345,1089,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87A7FFBC5A0E98456" box="[356,414,1089,1113]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87AAAFBC5A08F8455" bold="true" box="[433,504,1089,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Head.</emphasis>
Brown; eye bridge 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF879F1FBC6A2638455" box="[746,788,1090,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
facets wide. Antenna slightly paler, scape and pedicel yellowish; surface of flagellomeres rough, basal part of 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF8780FFBECA255848F" box="[788,802,1128,1152]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="4.0">4</number>
th flagellomere 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF878D7FBECA298848F" box="[972,1007,1128,1152]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.3">2.3</number>
times as long as wide, total length of flagellomere 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87A36FB09A04C84AA" box="[301,315,1165,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87A57FB08A0E684AA" box="[332,401,1164,1189]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1973,1996]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,193,1952]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Bradysia irwini, holotype, male. 8. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 9. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 10. Wing. 11. Gonostylus, ventral. 12. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87A98FB09A0E684AA" box="[387,401,1165,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87AB8FB09A0B184AA" box="[419,454,1165,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.8">2.8</number>
times as long as basal wide; setae on basal part of flagellomeres slightly shorter than width of flagellomeres with small sensilla among them. Maxillary palpus yellow; segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87F8DFB34A5D384C7" box="[1174,1188,1200,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
as long as segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87E9CFB34A4E084C7" box="[1415,1431,1200,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
, with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87BCAFB51A1A884E2" box="[209,223,1237,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
bristles and a dorsal flat patch of sensilla; segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87834FB51A24A84E2" box="[815,829,1237,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
with one long outer bristle; segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87FFCFB51A58284E2" box="[1255,1269,1237,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
is longest, 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87E62FB51A4EB84E2" box="[1401,1436,1237,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.3">1.3</number>
times as long as segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87AA6FB7CA0BB851F" box="[445,460,1272,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87AC7FB7CA342851E" bold="true" box="[476,565,1272,1297]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF8795EFB7CA3FA851F" box="[581,653,1272,1297]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1188,1211]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,534,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1341,515,1178]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Habitus of males, genitalia removed, lateral. 1. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype. 2. Bradysia irwini, holotype. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285013/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87967FB7CA3FA851F" box="[636,653,1272,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Yellow-brown, posterior gradually darkened; thoracic bristles pale. Posterior pronotum bare. Anterior pronotum with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF879CBFA99A3A9853A" box="[720,734,1309,1333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
bristles. Episternum 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF878CAFA99A2A8853A" box="[977,991,1309,1333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87F39FA98A547853A" box="[1058,1072,1308,1333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="6.0">6</number>
bristles. Mesonotum with some stronger dorsocentrals (broken and missing on 
<typeStatus id="54CDEBE7FFE4FFF879BDFAC4A27D8556" box="[678,778,1344,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">holotype</typeStatus>
) and with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF8789AFAC4A2DC8556" box="[897,939,1344,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
longer and some weaker laterals. Scutellum with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87BCFFAE1A1958572" box="[212,226,1381,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
strong and some shorter bristles. Katepisternum yellow coloured and as long as high. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87FF8FAE0A4538572" bold="true" box="[1251,1316,1380,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87E2CFAE0A4F88572" box="[1335,1423,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1973,1996]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,193,1952]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Bradysia irwini, holotype, male. 8. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 9. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 10. Wing. 11. Gonostylus, ventral. 12. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87E6BFAE1A4F88572" box="[1392,1423,1381,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Length = 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE4FFF87A1FFA0CA02A85AF" box="[260,349,1416,1441]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
; width/length = 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87904FA0CA32385AF" box="[543,596,1416,1440]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="0.4">0.40</number>
. Wing membrane transparent, without macrotrichia; anal area well developed; all posterior veins without macrotrichia; veins distinct except slight m-stem; R, R 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87FDCFA3FA5B885C6" box="[1223,1231,1467,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87E06FA3FA45285C6" box="[1309,1317,1467,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="5.0">5</number>
only with dorsal macrotrichia; R 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87A88FA66A0EC85FF" box="[403,411,1506,1520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
/R = 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87AC8FA57A37F85E4" box="[467,520,1491,1515]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="0.48">0.48</number>
; c/w = 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87941FA57A3F885E3" box="[602,655,1491,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="0.62">0.62</number>
; r-m/bM = 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF8780BFA57A23285E4" box="[784,837,1491,1515]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="0.77">0.77</number>
. Halteres brownish. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87F37FA57A51385E3" bold="true" box="[1068,1124,1491,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Legs</emphasis>
yellow; coxal bristles pale. Foretibia without small bristles among vestiture; tibial organ (
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87855FA7DA2E7861D" box="[846,912,1529,1554]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1973,1996]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,193,1952]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Bradysia irwini, holotype, male. 8. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 9. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 10. Wing. 11. Gonostylus, ventral. 12. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87899FA7EA2E7861D" box="[898,912,1530,1554]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a comb-like row of 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87FACFA7EA5B2861D" box="[1207,1221,1530,1554]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="9.0">9</number>
bristles, more than half of tibial apex wide. Tibial spur slightly longer than width of tibial apex of foretibia, apically slightly bent towards tibia. 
<collectingCountry id="F36115D5FFE4FFF87A2EF9C5A01A8655" box="[309,365,1601,1626]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with a posterodorsal row of dark bristles, extend 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF878D6F9C6A2878655" box="[973,1008,1602,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="0.7">0.7</number>
of tibial length. Claws with fine teeth. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87B8CF9E1A07B8671" bold="true" box="[151,268,1637,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87A00F9E1A0168671" box="[283,353,1637,1662]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1188,1211]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,534,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1341,515,1178]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Habitus of males, genitalia removed, lateral. 1. Bradysia similigibbosa, holotype. 2. Bradysia irwini, holotype. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285013/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87A4BF9E2A0168671" box="[336,353,1638,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Brown, with dark bristles. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF879B9F9E1A24A8671" bold="true" box="[674,829,1637,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87856F9E1A2D68671" box="[845,929,1637,1662]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1973,1996]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,193,1952]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Bradysia irwini, holotype, male. 8. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 9. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 10. Wing. 11. Gonostylus, ventral. 12. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87899F9E2A2D68671" box="[898,929,1638,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). As brown as abdomen. Gonocoxites longer than wide, normal setosity; ventral, inner-side of gonocoxites v-shaped and without basal lobe of bristles. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation id="134D49C0FFE4FFF87A31F929A00986C9" box="[298,382,1709,1734]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1973,1996]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,193,1952]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Bradysia irwini, holotype, male. 8. 4 th flagellomere, lateral. 9. Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 10. Wing. 11. Gonostylus, ventral. 12. Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87A78F92AA00986C9" box="[355,382,1710,1734]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrow, 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87AE9F929A35486C9" box="[498,547,1709,1734]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.75">2.75</number>
times as long as wide and swollen at middle; apex of gonostylus rounded, slightly bent inwards and subapically with 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE4FFF87961F956A3FF86E5" box="[634,648,1746,1770]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
equally long spines. Tegmen trapezoidal and membranous, with short and strongly sclerotized basal apodemes; area of teeth large, with strong, triangular teeth. Ejaculatory apodeme short and strong.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE4FFF87BDCF8BAA0EA8759" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,1986]" box="[199,413,1853,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87BDCF8BAA0468759" box="[199,305,1854,1878]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Body size</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE4FFF87A5BF8B9A0EE8759" box="[320,409,1853,1878]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE4FFF87BDCF8E6A0E98775" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,1986]" box="[199,414,1889,1914]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87BDCF8E6A06C8775" box="[199,283,1890,1914]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C06CEFFE4FFF87BDCF801A44987CD" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE4FFF87BDCF801A44987CD" blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,1986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE4FFF87BDCF801A0398791" bold="true" box="[199,334,1925,1950]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
We dedicate this new species to the collector Michael E. Irwin, Vail, Arizona [formerly of Urbana, Illinois] (
<collectingCountry id="F36115D5FFE4FFF87BE4F82EA04B87CD" box="[255,316,1962,1986]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">USA</collectingCountry>
), who sent us samples from different regions for our studies in the systematics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE4FFF87FD5F82DA44D87CD" box="[1230,1338,1961,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sciaridae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF0905CDFFE3FFFF7B8CF831A45687E5" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[227,1360,209,1927]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE3FFFF7B8CF831A45687E5" blockId="4.[151,1436,1973,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF7B8CF831A03E87C4" bold="true" box="[151,329,1973,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">FIGURES 8–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE3FFFF7A4AF831A08687C3" box="[337,497,1973,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF7A4AF831A08687C3" box="[337,497,1973,1996]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Bradysia irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, male. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF79B3F832A3CD87C4" bold="true" box="[680,698,1974,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">8.</emphasis>
4th flagellomere, lateral. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF78D1F832A2AB87C4" bold="true" box="[970,988,1974,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">9.</emphasis>
Tibial organ on inner-side of foretibia. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF7E67F832A4EB87C4" bold="true" box="[1404,1436,1974,1995]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">10.</emphasis>
Wing. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF7BC0F850A18F87E6" bold="true" box="[219,248,2004,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">11.</emphasis>
Gonostylus, ventral. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE3FFFF7AC9F850A08587E6" bold="true" box="[466,498,2004,2025]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">12.</emphasis>
Hypopygium, ventral. Scale bars: Figs 8, 9, 11, 12 = 0.1 mm; Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C36C06CEFFE2FFFE7BDCFF13A0268217" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC95545FFE2FFFE7BDCFF13A0268217" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7BDCFF13A03B80BF" bold="true" box="[199,332,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Discussion.</emphasis>
Amongst the New Caledonian sciarids, 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE783BFF1DA2F280A0" box="[800,901,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE783BFF1DA24680BF" box="[800,817,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7859FF1CA2F280A0" box="[834,901,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7F39FF1DA04580DB" authority="Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig, 2012" authorityName="Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F39FF1DA54480BF" box="[1058,1075,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F5FFF1CA5C580BF" box="[1092,1202,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig, 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE2FFFE7BE1FF38A04580DB" box="[250,306,188,212]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11048" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="in" value="2012.0">2012</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having two gonostylar spines (megasetae 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7828FF39A20680DB" box="[819,881,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">sensu</emphasis>
Vilkamaa 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE78F6FF39A55180DB" box="[1005,1062,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DBE4762FFE2FFFE7F35FF38A51C80DB" box="[1070,1131,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2012.0">2012</number>
c). This reduced number of gonostylar spines was construed as a unique feature of 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7818FF65A2E680F7" box="[771,913,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7818FF65A26380F7" box="[771,788,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7839FF64A2E680F7" box="[802,913,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the 
<collectingCountry id="F36115D5FFE2FFFE7F0EFF64A5B380F7" box="[1045,1220,223,248]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
sciarids (Vilkamaa 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7B8CFE81A1A58113" box="[151,210,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DBE4762FFE2FFFE7BC7FE80A06E8113" box="[220,281,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2012.0">2012</number>
c). 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7A21FE80A09B8113" box="[314,492,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7A21FE80A09B8113" box="[314,492,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Bradysia irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE782FFE81A2B28113" box="[820,965,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE782FFE81A2328113" box="[820,837,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE784DFE80A2B28113" box="[854,965,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer flagellomeres, the toothed claws, the inner-side of gonocoxites v-shaped and the slight subapical emargination of the gonostylus. Furthermore the c/w and r-m/bM ratios differ (c/w = 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE2FFFE7941FEC8A3DF816A" box="[602,680,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5748" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="in" value="0.62">0.62 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE79ABFEC9A264816B" box="[688,787,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE79ABFEC9A3B6816B" box="[688,705,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE79CBFEC9A264816B" box="[720,787,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. c/w = 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE2FFFE789DFEC8A563816A" box="[902,1044,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9684999999999997" metricValueMax="2.159" metricValueMin="1.7779999999999998" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="in" value="0.7749999999999999" valueMax="0.85" valueMin="0.7">0.70–0.85 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7F07FEC9A5DD816B" box="[1052,1194,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F07FEC9A55A816B" box="[1052,1069,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F27FEC8A5DD816B" box="[1084,1194,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; r-m/bM = 
<quantity id="4C8EF8A0FFE2FFFE7E36FEC8A40B816A" box="[1325,1404,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9558" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="in" value="0.77">0.77 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7E9FFEC9A1AD8188" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7E9FFEC9A4E2816B" box="[1412,1429,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7B8CFEF4A1AD8188" box="[151,218,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. both veins subequal in 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE791DFEF5A3E48187" box="[518,659,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE791DFEF5A3608187" box="[518,535,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE793FFEF4A3E48187" box="[548,659,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE785FFEF5A2A78187" box="[836,976,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemellata">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE785FFEF5A2228187" box="[836,853,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7879FEF4A2A78187" box="[866,976,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">gemellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7F6FFEF5A5AC8187" box="[1140,1243,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F6FFEF5A5F28187" box="[1140,1157,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7F89FEF4A5AC8187" box="[1170,1243,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7E21FEF5A4EB8188" box="[1338,1436,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irwini">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7E21FEF5A43C8187" box="[1338,1355,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7E42FEF4A4EB8188" box="[1369,1436,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">irwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be placed in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7ABCFE11A34381A3" box="[423,564,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungicola">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7ABCFE11A0CF81A3" box="[423,440,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7AD1FE10A34381A3" box="[458,564,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">fungicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7991FE11A3BF81A3" box="[650,712,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">sensu</emphasis>
Menzel &amp; Mohrig (
<number id="3DBE4762FFE2FFFE78A2FE10A28081A3" box="[953,1015,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2000.0">2000</number>
). Characters like the long bristle on segment 
<number id="3DBE4762FFE2FFFE7BE5FE3CA07981DF" box="[254,270,440,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2.0">2</number>
, claws with fine teeth and the v-shaped gonocoxal inner-side support this classification, although the absence of bristles in the vestiture of the foretibia and the trapezoidal tegmen are not typical characters of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C762EC6FFE2FFFE7E9FFE59A0768217" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungicola">
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7E9FFE59A4E281FB" box="[1412,1429,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9028957FFE2FFFE7B8CFD84A0768217" box="[151,257,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">fungicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
